approvals.title: Fran Worley is now the admin for CAS
Yarn install deploy step takes over 9 minutes on staging!

comments.body: On lib-approvals-staging2, yarn quickly installs all the dependencies.  However, after all directories are present in node_modules, it spends several minutes maxing out the CPU.
Prod could be fast because `yarn install` is a disk-heavy operation, and prod is on the nice new HPE Alletra storage.

Interestingly, `npm i` is much faster on these boxes: 2 minutes without a package-lock.json, 35 seconds with one.  This is compared to 4 minutes for `yarn install` with a yarn.lock and with plenty of packages already available in `/home/deploy/.cache`.

pulfalight.title: Update aeon URL per atlas recommendation.
Non Princeton Aeon Users lose their Shopping Cart

comments.body:
Atlas tech support recommends we do the following. Update our code to only submit the following params a single time in a given post:

AeonForm
DocumentType
GroupingIdentifier
GroupingOption_CallNumber
GroupingOption_ItemDate
GroupingOption_ItemInfo1
GroupingOption_ItemInfo3
GroupingOption_ItemInfo4
GroupingOption_ItemNumber
GroupingOption_ItemTitle
GroupingOption_ItemVolume
GroupingOption_Location
GroupingOption_ReferenceNumber
GroupingOption_Site
Location
RequestType
SubmitButton
SystemID
UserReview
WebRequestForm

Currently we submit these params for every container included in a given POST request. Additionally they recommend the values for these two params should be set to the following values:
AeonForm=EADRequest
WebRequestForm=ExternalRequest

Hi Hector, I have added the field according to the code snippet that you added to the initial ticket. Happy to pair once we have some time to see this one through the finish line, as I am not sure if all acceptance criteria has been met. Thanks!
